news.title: Dehradun civic body's online services not user-friendly, say residents
news.para: DMC started the online house tax payment facility in February 2021. Apart from public convenience, the move was aimed at reducing crowds at its office, especially in light of the pandemic.

news.title: PNB Housing's Rs 2,500 crore rights issue expected to be complete by Dec: Official
news.para: Following the rights issue, the shareholding of Punjab National Bank (PNB) as a promoter of the company would come down from the current level of 32.57 per cent to below 30 per cent.

news.title: DLF's net profit up 39% at Rs 469.57 crore in Q1 FY23
news.para: In a statement, DLF said its sales bookings jumped two-fold to Rs 2,040 crore during the April-June period of this fiscal year, compared with the year-ago period.

news.title: 315Work Avenue lease out 22,000 sq ft co-working space to MoEngage
news.para: 315Work Avenue currently manages around 30,000 seats spread over 1.5 million sq ft in Bengaluru, Mumbai and Pune. It plans to double its portfolio over a period of next one year.

news.title: Ludhiana: Vigilance books LIT ex-chief, five others for illegal sale of plots
news.para: Balasubramanium is a close aide of former cabinet minister Bharat Bhushan Ashu of the Congress. Sharma has been arrested in this case and further investigation is under progress.

news.title: Huda to auction 29 shops in Panchkula on August 3
news.para: Huda officials said according to the initial plan, NFS will be set up in 1.25 acre in Sector 5. In total, Huda is planning for 60 shops, but in the first phase, 29 shops will be auctioned.

news.title: Will start agitation if demands not met, warn realtors in Punjab
news.para: The main agenda of the meeting was to chalk out a strategy against the non-fulfilment of their demands like waiving off condition for submitting NOCs for registries, reducing the collector rates that have been recently hiked by the state government.

news.title: Chandigarh administration seeks status of vacant properties, auction details
news.para: ​​In Chandigarh, collector rates are the parameters for auctioning of land for commercial, institutional and cultural purposes.

news.title: Nashik civic body to focus on rainwater harvesting in residential complexes
news.para: As per the unified development control promotions & regulations (UDCPR), the rainwater harvesting system is mandatory for buildings on plots of 500 sq metres or more.

news.title: Jaipur development body plans townships on Tonk, Phagi roads using land pooling
news.para: An official said, “The central government is providing incentives to the state to plans under land pooling. Both the townships are proposed to be developed under this scheme. The Centre will contribute its share of Rs 1 crore, which will be provided to appoint the consultancy.”

news.title: Construction of PMAY houses in Punjab, Haryana & Himachal Pradesh marred by slow pace of work
news.para: Out of 3,02,502 houses sanctioned in the three states, only 1,15,645 have been completed. The region’s completion rate of 38.22% is far lower than the national average of 50%.

news.title: Plot allottees allege discrimination by Bengaluru development body
news.para: In fact, allottees of sites in NPKL are outraged that BDA is speeding up work at DSKL, though no one has bought a site there. Meanwhile, their layout has been under utter neglect even though they paid for the plots six years ago.

news.title: West Bengal government to soon auction several land parcels in Alipore
news.para: The Housing Infrastructure Development Corporation (Hidco) has fixed a starting bid price of Rs 236.7 crore for a 5.6 acre plot at the rate of Rs 42.3 crore per acre.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves ULPIN for land parcels, rollout next month
news.para: Confirming the development, state settlement commissioner N K Sudhanshu told TOI that a GR (government resolution) had been issued on the Unique Land Parcel Identification Number (ULPIN).

news.title: Land sold after undertaking development activities should attract 18% GST: Madhya Pradesh AAAR
news.para: Any land sold after undertaking development activities such as providing water line, electricity or sanitation facility should attract 18% GST, Madhya Pradesh AAAR ruled.
